I hear what you are saying Dalynia, but that is a bit black and white (as was Wolfy).  There are times when as an Enchanter you just don't have TIME to mess with extra stuns and using the mana to remez things while the pet gets on the correct target. (I am thinking 3 or 4 mobs here, high enough level you don't want to ae mez as an example)  In these cases it sometimes IS best to just let the pet tank the mob while you deal with the rest of the pull.<br>
<br>
I like Mages, but I have played with some of the best (including our server BotB mage), and one hallmark of all of those mages was that they played very well with enchanters and none of them were at all afraid to kill their pet instantly if it looked like they were involved in something group threatening. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uchingwon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chingwon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/15/02 7:45:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=622.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: RE: Wolfypaw</span><hr size=1> Bah had to stop reading after half of this cuz it is all redundant.<br>
<br>
Basically I'm just going to say that &quot;i did this to save the group&quot; while good in that situation is pointless.  Your grp is counting on you to do those things, and so you normally are going to be put into that position.<br>
<br>
Mages do have plenty that they can do and i'll repeat like everyone else that it's all about the pets, but tis also about mana management.  If I'm in a grp i don't stop pulling because the mage says he is OOM.  I tell em to spread things out a bit better.  If a mage can't control his pet (or any pet class for that matter, although I have yet to come across a BL that can't control their pet /shrug) then you can be damn sure that 3 strikes yer out /punt.<br>
<br>
Another reason I think people prefer melee over caster+pet is  that they're a consistent amount of damage.  You know that every single mob is going to receive this amt of dmg from this person, and they don't tend to overnuke, and take lots and lots of mana from the healers.  (Happens all the time on caster classes /bonk)<br>
<br>
Bah I'm rambling.  Point is, we should all be monks. <p>Grandmaster Baron Chingwon<br>
