<br>
When I play my enchanter, I seriously HATE beastlord pets.<br>
<br>
Here's the thing, as a melee class you are right up in the mobs face, you have to keep the mob targetted and autoattack on.   As a melee you don't have a full scope of the battle the way a normal pet caster does when he is sitting in the corner.   <br>
<br>
You can argue all you want about the skill of the player.  The fact is the spam comes across a melee screen so fast they don't know which mob has hit them and how often, much less be able to see the mez messages every single time.  So when one mob is dead, BOOM - pet is running all over breaking mez for the main tank and the enchanter is taking a pounding.<br>
<br>
Now maybe in those groups where it's single pulls forever a BL has the same ammount of control that a regular pet caster does.  However, I don't like those groups - I want the puller bringing back 3+ mobs every time, I like fast paced xp action with no down time.  In those situations, BL pets are going haywire and forcing me to keep every mob rooted down as well as mezd.   Sorry, but I don't like having to do more work because the BL isn't paying attention.<br>
